{{Shrine |name = Murakami Shrine |image = {{Image Needed|cat=Kakamigahara City}} |location = {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県}}{{ill|Kakamigahara City|ja|各務原市}}{{ill|Nakachozukacho|ja|那加長塚町}}1-chome 64 |position = |enshrined_deity = {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|lt=Iwanagahime|lt_ja=石長比女神}} |shrine_rank = {{ill|Kinpeisha|ja|金幣社|lt=Hakuhesha|lt_ja=白幣社}}<ref name="Shiterikyo Shrine">Pilgrimage Guide of the Shiterikyo Shrine, the Chief Shrine of Naka in Mino Province</ref>・Former Village Shrine |founding = Unknown |main_hall = |alternative_name = |fuda = |annual_festival = |religious_services = }}
'''Murakami Shrine''' (村上神社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Gifu Prefecture|ja|岐阜県}}{{ill|Kakamigahara City|ja|各務原市}}{{ill|Nakachozukacho|ja|那加長塚町}}.
== Overview == {{ill|Kakamigahara City|ja|各務原市}}{{ill|Nakachozukacho|ja|那加長塚町}} (formerly ({{ill|Kakami District|ja|各務郡}} Nagatsuka Village)) is the tutelary deity of the area and is enshrined approximately 300 m (about 5 minutes on foot) to the west of {{ill|Shiterikyo Shrine (Kakamigahara)|ja|手力雄神社 (各務原市)|lt=Shiterikyo Shrine|lt_ja=手力雄神社}}, the head shrine of the {{ill|Naka Town|ja|那加町|lt=Naka Area|lt_ja=那加地区}}. The founding date is unknown. In {{ill|1934|ja|1934年}} (Showa 9), it was designated as a village shrine. The shrine precincts contain many exposed bedrocks, and some of the rocks—for example, one whose shape resembles {{ill|Donkotsu|ja|ドンコ|lt=Donkotsu|lt_ja=ドンコツ}} and is revered as a {{ill|Mountain Deity|ja|山神}}—serve as objects of worship. Although the shrine is named “Murakami Shrine” (村上神社), the name inscribed on the shrine plaque and gate posts is “Murakami Shrine” (村神神社).
== Enshrined Deity == * {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|lt=Iwanagahime|lt_ja=石長比女神}}
== Sub-Shrines == * {{ill|Akiba Shrine|ja|秋葉神社}}
== Major Religious Events == * February – Prayer for a Good Year Festival * June – Rice-Planting Festival * September – Annual Festival * December – Niiname-sai
== Footnotes == {{Reflist}}
== External Links == * [https://www.gifu-jinjacho.jp/syosai.php?shrno=766&shrname=%E2%98%85%E6%9D%91%E4%B8%8A%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE%E2%98%85 Murakami Shrine (Gifu Prefecture Shrine Office)]
{{shinto-stub}}
