== Overview == {{ill|Kakamigahara City|ja|各務原市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kakamigahara City|qq=}}{{ill|Nakachozukacho|ja|那加長塚町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakachozukacho|qq=}} (formerly ({{ill|Kakami District|ja|各務郡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kakami District|qq=}} Nagatsuka Village)) is the tutelary deity of the area and is enshrined approximately 300 m (about 5 minutes on foot) to the west of {{ill|Shiterikyo Shrine (Kakamigahara)|ja|手力雄神社 (各務原市)|lt=Shiterikyo Shrine|lt_ja=手力雄神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiterikyo Shrine (Kakamigahara)|qq=}}, the head shrine of the {{ill|Naka Town|ja|那加町|lt=Naka Area|lt_ja=那加地区|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naka Town|qq=}}. The founding date is unknown. In {{ill|1934|ja|1934th year|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1934|qq=}} (Showa 9), it was designated as a village shrine. The shrine precincts contain many exposed bedrocks, and some of the rocks—for example, one whose shape resembles {{ill|Donkotsu|ja|ドンコ|lt=Donkotsu|lt_ja=ドンコツ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Donkotsu|qq=}} and is revered as a {{ill|Mountain Deity|ja|山神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mountain Deity|qq=}}—serve as objects of worship. Although the shrine is named “Murakami Shrine” (村上神社), the name inscribed on the shrine plaque and gate posts is “Murakami Shrine” (村神神社).
== Enshrined Deity == * {{ill|Iwanagahime|ja|イワナガヒメ|1=Iwanaga-hime|lt=Iwanagahime|lt_ja=石長比女神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwanagahime|13=User:Immanuelle/Iwanaga-hime|qq=}}
