== Overview == [[:en:Kakamigahara|Kakamigahara City]]{{ill|Nakachozukacho|ja|那加長塚町|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nakachozukacho|qq=}} (formerly ({{ill|Kakami District|ja|各務郡|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kakami District|qq=}} Nagatsuka Village)) is the tutelary deity of the area and is enshrined approximately 300 m (about 5 minutes on foot) to the west of {{ill|Shiterikyo Shrine (Kakamigahara)|ja|手力雄神社 (各務原市)|lt=Shiterikyo Shrine|lt_ja=手力雄神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiterikyo Shrine (Kakamigahara)|qq=}}, the head shrine of the {{ill|Naka Town|ja|那加町|lt=Naka Area|lt_ja=那加地区|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Naka Town|qq=}}. The founding date is unknown. In [[:en:1934|1934]] (Showa 9), it was designated as a village shrine. The shrine precincts contain many exposed bedrocks, and some of the rocks—for example, one whose shape resembles [[:en:Dark sleeper|Donkotsu]] and is revered as a {{ill|Mountain Deity|ja|山神|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mountain Deity|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 山の神}}—serve as objects of worship. Although the shrine is named “Murakami Shrine” (村上神社), the name inscribed on the shrine plaque and gate posts is “Murakami Shrine” (村神神社).
== Enshrined Deity == * [[:en:Iwanaga-hime|Iwanagahime]] [[ja:村上神社_(各務原市那加長塚町)]]
== Sub-Shrines == * {{ill|Akiba Shrine|ja|秋葉神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Akiba Shrine|qq=}}
== Major Religious Events == * February – Prayer for a Good Year Festival * June – Rice-Planting Festival * September – Annual Festival * December – Niiname-sai
== Footnotes == {{Reflist}}
